ion Circle – North York Central Library\n	\n\n\n					\n	\n		North York Central Library	\n	\n		5120 Yonge Street\, Toronto\, Ontario\, Canada	\n	\n					\n\n	\n					\n				_Adults	\n\n				\n\n				\n	Are you new to Canada as a Permanent Resident or a Convention Refugee? Every Monday at the North York Central Library there will be free weekly sessions to prepare for […] \n\n				\n			\n		\n	\n\n\n\n							\n				\n				\n\n	\n	\n		\n			Tue		\n		\n			17		\n	\n\n\n	\n		\n			\n	\n\n\n			\n\n				\n					\n	\n		Looking For Volunteers: Content Creator Crew!	\n\n					\n		\n		March 17 @ 2:00 pm - 4:00 pm	\n	\n\n	\n		\n\n	\n	\n	\n\n		Looking For Volunteers: Content Creator Crew!\n	\n\n\n					\n	\n		Parkdale Library	\n	\n		1303 Queen Street West\, Toronto\, Ontario\, Canada	\n	\n					\n\n	\n					\n				_Youth	\n\n				\n\n				\n	Love TikTok + Instagram? Turn your creativity into real experience What you'll do: Take photos + short videos Capture behind-the-scenes moments Help edit Reels/TikToks (simple + guided) Support social media […] \n\n				\n			\n		\n	\n\n\n\n							\n				\n				\n\n	\n	\n		\n			Tue		\n		\n			17		\n	\n\n\n	\n		\n			\n	\n\n\n			\n\n				\n					\n	\n		Youth Connect Hub	\n\n					\n		\n		March 17 @ 3:30 pm - 5:30 pm	\n	\n\n	\n		\n\n	\n	\n	\n\n		Youth Connect Hub\n	\n\n\n					\n	\n		CultureLink Children & Youth Centre	\n	\n		3535 Dundas Street West\, Toronto\, Ontario\, Canada	\n	\n					\n\n	\n					\n				_Youth	\n\n				\n\n				\n	A safe and welcoming space for youth to connect\, relax\, and have fun. Enjoy group games\, creative activities\, food sessions\, and conversations that support emotional well-being and confidence. For Newcomer […] \n\n				\n			\n		\n	\n\n\n\n							\n				\n				\n\n	\n	\n		\n			Tue		\n		\n			17		\n	\n\n\n	\n		\n			\n	\n\n\n			\n\n				\n					\n	\n		English Conversation Circle – Forest Hill Library	\n\n					\n		\n		March 17 @ 6:00 pm - 7:30 pm	\n	\n\n	\n		\n\n	\n	\n	\n\n		English Conversation Circle – Forest Hill Library\n	\n\n\n										\n\n	\n					\n				_Adults	\n\n				\n\n				\n	Are you new to Canada as a Permanent Resident or a Convention Refugee? Practice English in small groups\, with the support of our Mentors! 8 weekly sessions Speak with confidence […] \n\n				\n			\n		\n	\n\n\n\n							\n				\n				\n\n	\n	\n		\n			Tue		\n		\n			17		\n	\n\n\n	\n		\n			\n	\n\n\n			\n\n				\n					\n	\n		Citizenship Education Circle – Toronto Reference Library	\n\n					\n		\n		March 17 @ 6:00 pm - 8:30 pm	\n	\n\n	\n		\n\n	\n	\n	\n\n		Citizenship Education Circle – Toronto Reference Library\n	\n\n\n					\n	\n		Toronto Reference Library	\n	\n		789 Yonge Street\, Toronto\, Ontario\, Canada	\n	\n					\n\n	\n					\n				_Adults	\n\n				\n\n				\n	Are you new to Canada as a Permanent Resident or a Convention Refugee? Every Tuesday at the Toronto Reference Library there will be free weekly sessions to prepare for the […] \n\n				\n			\n		\n	\n\n\n\n							\n				\n				\n\n	\n	\n		\n			Wed		\n		\n			18		\n	\n\n\n	\n		\n			\n	\n\n\n			\n\n				\n					\n	\n		Networking Event with BMO	\n\n					\n		\n		March 18 @ 1:00 pm - 3:30 pm	\n	\n					\n	\n		CultureLink	\n	\n		2340 Dundas St W\, Toronto\, Ontario\, Canada	\n	\n					\n\n	\n					\n				_Adults	\n\n				\n\n				\n	Come join us for a networking event with professionals from BMO! Who can participate: Internationally trained professionals Permanent Resident or Convention Refugees At least 19 years of age Job-ready English […] \n\n				\n			\n		\n	\n\n\n\n							\n				\n				\n\n	\n	\n		\n			Wed		\n		\n			18		\n	\n\n\n	\n		\n			\n	\n\n\n			\n\n				\n					\n	\n		Create Learn Connect	\n\n					\n		\n		March 18 @ 2:00 pm - 4:00 pm	\n	\n\n	\n		\n\n	\n	\n	\n\n		Create Learn Connect\n	\n\n\n					\n	\n		Cecil Street Community Centre	\n	\n		58 Cecil Street\, Toronto\, Ontario\, Canada	\n	\n					\n\n	\n					\n				_Adults	\n\n				\n\n				\n	Nurture Your Artistic Potential! Our thoughtfully designed Art Workshops encourage creativity\, focus\, and growth Participants must be a Permanent Resident or Convention Refugee and at least 19 years old. To […] \n\n				\n			\n		\n	\n\n\n\n							\n				\n				\n\n	\n	\n		\n			Thu		\n		\n			19		\n	\n\n\n	\n		\n			\n			\n\n				\n					\n	\n		March Break Camp	\n\n					\n		\n		March 19 @ 9:00 am - 6:00 pm	\n	\n					\n	\n		CultureLink Children & Youth Centre	\n	\n		3535 Dundas Street West\, Toronto\, Ontario\, Canada	\n	\n					\n\n	\n					\n				_Youth	\n\n				\n\n				\n	For Newcomer kids and youth who are Permanent Residents or Convention Refugees! We will have: Full Day Programs Leadership & Teamwork Activities Art Workshops Ping Pong\, Foosball Shevchenko Musuem Tour […] \n\n				\n			\n		\n	\n\n\n\n							\n				\n				\n\n	\n	\n		\n			Thu		\n		\n			19		\n	\n\n\n	\n		\n			\n	\n\n\n			\n\n				\n					\n	\n		G1 Driving Test Classes for Newcomers	\n\n					\n		\n		March 19 @ 2:00 pm - 4:00 pm	\n	\n\n	\n		\n\n	\n	\n	\n\n		G1 Driving Test Classes for Newcomers\n	\n\n\n					\n	\n		CultureLink	\n	\n		2340 Dundas St W\, Toronto\, Ontario\, Canada	\n	\n					\n\n	\n					\n				_Adults	\n\n				\n\n				\n	Get ready to pass your Ontario G1 Knowledge Test for Free! Program Highlights: Instructor-led\, easy-to-follow lessons MTO-approved materials Supportive and welcoming learning environment Ideal for first-time drivers and newcomers Who […] \n\n				\n			\n		\n	\n\n\n\n							\n				\n				\n\n	\n	\n		\n			Thu		\n		\n			19		\n	\n\n\n	\n		\n			\n	\n\n\n			\n\n				\n					\n	\n		Content Creation for Success	\n\n					\n		\n		March 19 @ 4:00 pm - 5:00 pm	\n	\n\n	\n		\n\n	\n	\n	\n\n		Content Creation for Success\n	\n\n\n					\n	\n		CultureLink Children & Youth Centre	\n	\n		3535 Dundas Street West\, Toronto\, Ontario\, Canada	\n	\n					\n\n	\n					\n				_Youth	\n\n				\n\n				\n	Free Workshops For Youth\, Ages 16-30 Learn directly from real influencers! Live Q&A - ask creators anything (growth\, money\, fame) Secrets behind viral videos + follower growth Film + edit […] \n\n				\n			\n		\n	\n\n\n\n							\n				\n				\n\n	\n	\n		\n			Thu		\n		\n			19		\n	\